  "text": "A previous systematic review explored the pharmacokinetic profiles of oral 5-ASA formulations including urinary and faecal excretion [CITATION_1] . In the present systematic review, we aim to explore whether the mucosal and/or faecal 5-ASA concentrations correlate with disease activity and/or therapeutic efficacy in patients with IBD, and thus have potential for TDM in UC patients. ",
